      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional safeguard that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon core liberties even if it follows proper procedure. It has been instrumental in recognizing rights like privacy and bodily autonomy, which are not explicitly listed in the Constitution. This doctrine allows the courts to strike down laws that infringe upon deeply held individual freedoms, thereby expanding the scope of American liberty.",
      "source": "target",
